node_modules
# dist/ is INTENTIONALLY committed until npm publish (D7) is sorted.
# Reason: consumers fetch this package via 'github:ZwingD/cms-revalidate-nextjs#<sha>'
# until it's on the npm registry. Without a committed dist, the install
# would have to run tsup at install time, which OOMs Vercel's build
# machine on small consumer projects (observed on feezy-website 2026-05-23).
# Once published to npm, restore the `dist` gitignore line.
*.tsbuildinfo
.npmrc
.env
.env.local
.DS_Store
coverage
.vscode
.idea
